text: Input/Output Data The input/output data is the type of data an agent expects and delivers. The agent produces the UDR types selected from the UDR Type list. MIM Publishes The agent publishes the following MIM parameters: MIM Parameter Description MIM Parameter Description Database This MIM parameter contains the name of he database the agent is collecting from. Database is of the string type and is defined as a global MIM context type. Table This MIM parameter contains the name of the working table the agent is collecting from. Table is of the string type and is defined as a global MIM context type. Source Filename This MIM parameter contains the name of the currently processed file, as defined at the source. Source Filename is of the string type and is defined as a header MIM context type. Accesses The agent does access MIM resources if MIM parameter assignments are set in the Parameter Editor in the Condition tab.
